    <Paragraph  Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
        Syncfusion Essential Edit WPF
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph  >
        Essential Edit for WPF can be used as a basic editor that includes all the basic editor features such as
        <Run FontWeight="Bold">text editing, cutting, copying and pasting</Run> . It enables users to open and save files from and to a variety of file formats. The edit control has built-in commands that can be bound with command bindings to perform various operations such as
        <Run FontWeight="Bold">Open, New, Save, Copy, Cut, Paste, Select All</Run> , and so on.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph  >
        Essential Edit for WPF provides built-in support for common .NET programming languages such as C#, Visual Basic, XAML, XML, and SQL. With built-in language support, the edit control also provides syntax highlighting and expand-collapse support.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph  >
        Support for automatic IntelliSense with C# languages is built-in, and the control comes with a custom IntelliSense mode for all supported languages. Essential Edit for WPF provides full-fledged customization options to users so they can create custom language configurations and implement custom expand-collapse operations for those custom languages.
    </Paragraph>

